      "side": 1,
      "message": "I specifically don\u0027t want to mention what\u0027s child and what\u0027s parent because they are arbitrarily defined and not even visible to the end users.\n\nConsider:\n  core.builder(\"b\", triggered_by\u003d[\"t\"])\n\nIt will produce the following error:\n  core.builder(\"b\") in \"triggered_by\" refers to undefined core.trigger(\"t\")\n\nSimilarly this:\n  core.trigger(\"t\", triggers\u003d[\"b\"])\n\nWill produce:\n  core.trigger(\"t\") in \"triggers\" refers to undefined core.builder(\"b\")\n\nThese errors messages look (relatively) clear and consistent to the end user (who has no idea what is \u0027parent\u0027 and \u0027child\u0027). Compare them to (respectively):\n\n  relation \"triggered_by\" from core.trigger(\"t\") to core.builder(\"b\"): parent does not exist\n  relation \"triggered_by\" from core.trigger(\"t\") to core.builder(\"b\"): child does not exist\n\nWhat parent, what child?..\n\nAnyway, as said in TODO, I expect there\u0027ll be a separate CL later (when everything is in place) that cleans up how errors are presented, so all looks consistent and the graph terminology doesn\u0027t leak into the tool output.",
